		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Not really.  I don't feel like working on something after work if I'm too tired. And similar to MetalSlime, having a kid (2 years 1/2) and a day job in japan makes it harder to code during the night since public transport + the job takes a good part of your day.
<br />
<br />I was liking that during college days (working at night, not being tired) and could program until 3am in the morning, waking up and going to school after but now if I do that for a few days.. Forget it, I feel sick.  That doesn't leave much time for hobbies which mean either during lunch time or late at night if you can still focus.

		

